      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You can perform a simple check by asking him to smile broadly and raise both arms simultaneously; look for any drooping on one side of his face or weakness in his arm. If he struggles to do these simple movements, it's a red flag for neurological issues. Because you cannot definitively rule out a stroke or other serious condition at home, the safest course of action is to get him checked out by a medical professional right now.",
      "source": "target",
